          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript used in private or public recitation and prayer focused on the veneration and praise of the Hindu deity Śiva. A mystical text of 50 verses considered to have been written when the author Appayya Dīkṣita was intoxicated. Opening benediction is to Śiva rather than Gaṇeśa, as is common in Sanskrit manuscripts.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Ātmārapaṇastuti</title>
              <title type="vernacular">आत्मारपणस्तुति</title>
              <author>
                <persName type="authority">Appayya Dīkṣita</persName>
              </author>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti śrīmadadvaitācāryaśrīmadappayyadīkṣitaviracitā ātmārpaṇastutiḥ samāptā / (f. 4v).</colophon>
